reviewText: Impressive collection of concerts and video, with excellent audio production.  Once Iced Earth gets a hold on you, there is no going back to an existence without it!  Be sure to check out Jon Schaffer's solo project, Sons of Liberty "Brush-Fires of the Mind"Brush-Fires of the Mind.  With a new Iced Earth CD being released this year, and a Sons of Liberty EP with 5 new songs, prepare to be blowing out some speakers!
summary: Must have for all Iced Earth Fans

reviewText: Although, i have the 'Alive In Athens' dvd, it's nice to have a official release. It looks weird to see Matt sing these songs with his short hair, but his voice still holds up. The Ripper part could have used a little better sound though. All in all, a great dvd!!

reviewText: yes believe all the positive reviews...3 complete shows , 2 dvd's , over 5 hours of pure a** kicking iced earth metal. finally a metal compilation to rival the classic "alive in athens". both tim and matt have now left the band and wishing good luck to the new vocalist stu block and the new album DYSTOPIA on the way. thanks to john schaffer for having the balls to keep putting out great metal music when the music situation in america is so pitiful with "wannabe and pop/shallow" crap ruling the walking dead.
